      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 5-6 min, remove the orzo from the oven and top with the <strong>garlicky salmon</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and put the dish back in the oven to cook for a further 14-15 min or until the stock has been absorbed and the orzo and salmon is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
